cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the efficacy of adversarial attacks on convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and proofs, indicating that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
